        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:19PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Meldrim, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pooler, Richmond Hill, I-16/I-95 Interchange, Godley Station,
Savannah International Airport, Downtown Savannah, Garden City,
Port Wentworth, Bloomingdale and Meldrim.

This includes the following highways...
I-16 between mile markers 148 and 161.
I-95 in Georgia between mile markers 91 and 108.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
